Sentencas: Co-improving the structural stability and electrocatalytic activity of anode materials is a major challenge for the development of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Co-improving the electrocatalytic performance and H2S tolerance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a novel anode material Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.4Ti0.1O6-delta (SFMT) is designed and prepared by using Ti to replace Mo of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM).
Titulo: Co-improving the electrocatalytic performance and H2S tolerance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ti doping effectively enhances the ability of SFM to resist H2S corrosion and SFMT maintains the desired perovskite structure after being exposed to H2S (1000 ppm).
Titulo: Co-improving the electrocatalytic performance and H2S tolerance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the partial replacement of Mo5+/Mo6+ by Ti4+ ions can also improve the concentration of oxygen vacancies and enhance the oxygen ion surface exchange and bulk diffusion capabilities.
Titulo: Co-improving the electrocatalytic performance and H2S tolerance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SFMT-based SOFC delivers an excellent power output in H-2 containing 500 ppm H2S and stably operates for a long time (>50 h), resulting in a maximum power density of 0.71 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Co-improving the electrocatalytic performance and H2S tolerance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The current study presents a promising material design strategy for developing high-performance SOFC anodes.
Titulo: Co-improving the electrocatalytic performance and H2S tolerance of a Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ based anode for solid oxide fuel cells
